Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at Emory University in Atlanta, Georgia, addressing the recent shootings that took place in the state. She condemned the violence and highlighted the fact that six of the eight victims were of Asian descent and seven were women. Harris also acknowledged the rise in hate crimes and discrimination against Asian Americans over the past year, with 3,800 incidents being reported. She emphasized that racism, xenophobia, and sexism have always existed in America and called for treating everyone with dignity and respect. Harris concluded by stating that harm against any individual is harm against all, and she vowed to speak out against violence, hate crimes, and discrimination.